    "overview_number": 4,
    "overview_title": "Magnificent Magnitude",
    "overview_subtitle": "Absolute Value",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students develop a conceptual understanding of absolute value and calculate the absolute value of numbers. They interpret the meaning of absolute values as the magnitude for a positive or negative quantity in a real-world context and use absolute value to solve real-world problems. Students compare absolute value expressions using inequality symbols."
  },
