      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "The absolute value of a number is the number’s distance from zero on a number line.",
          "In everyday life, we often use absolute value statements to describe changes and comparisons of values.",
          "You can use an absolute value expression to calculate the distance between positive and negative numbers in various contexts.",
          "You can compare absolute value expressions by using the definition of absolute value and number lines."
        ]
